  "content": "If you Google \"Michelle Williams\", the first results that come up refer to the actor who has starred in Brokeback Mountain and Blue Valentine. But there is another Michelle Williams. The former Destiny's Child singer, and current multi-million selling gospel megastar, stage actor, and (who knew?) owner of a Chicago basketball team. When she falls over, she looks like this: About a year ago, the Tumblr Poor Michelle was established to collate all the times Poor Michelle was treated poorly. Or, as they put it, \"all the times Michelle got the short end of the Destiny's Child stick\". And you know what they mean. While Beyonc\u00e9's and Kelly's outfits matched, Michelle's outfit would always look like it was cobbled together from the off-cuts. While two-and-a-half-minutes of a three-minute pop video would encompass 99% Beyonc\u00e9 and Kelly close-ups, Michelle would struggle to get an elbow in shot. At the 2013 Super Bowl performance, Michelle's microphone was turned down, which is a bit like giving a cop a water gun instead of a real gun, and patting him on the head. We all recognise ourselves in Poor Michelle: the wallflower at the dance; the one to be picked last for the football team and then made to be a goal post. And this week, the #PoorMichelle hashtag started to trend again: Official response from Michelle Williams And then, finally, after almost a year of dignified silence, Michelle Williams responded:",
